1970-01-01 00:40:00 Preheat your oven to 200 °C or gas mark 6

Air the chicken for at least 10 minutes out of the fridge before you start cooking

Boil a kettle

Heat a large hob and over safe casserole dish at a high heat on the hob with vegetable oil.

Peel and chop the brown onions into wedges

Chop the tomatoes into wedges

Add to the casserole dish with a pinch of salt to taste

Crush the garlic cloves and remove the skins

Crush the cardamom pods to open them with the side of a knife

Add the crush garlic, cardamom pods to the dish, along with the ground turmeric, ground coriander, curry power and chilli flakes (add the chilli flakes to your preferred heat!)

Sprinkle in chicken stock, add chopped tomatoes, a pinch of sugar and 100 ml of boiled water

Add the diced chicken breast and bring to a boil over a high heat.

Once boiling, put the pot into the oven and cook for 30-35 minutes, until the check is cooked through and the sauce has thickened.

Once cooked, discard the cardamom pods and serve with your choice extras, such as rice, naan bread, popadoms or side dishes such as aloo saag.
